.TH GENERATE_HTML 1 "March 2026" "AutoReadme" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
generate_html \- Convert README.md to HTML files for Apache web servers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B generate_html
[\fB\-\-create_header\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B generate_html
processes README.md and creates HTML files for Apache web server directory listings:
.IP \(bu 2
.B .header.html
Contains the project title (first header section)
.IP \(bu 2
.B .readme.html
Full README content excluding the "## Files ##" section
.PP
All content is processed through the b4markdown preprocessor before HTML conversion.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-create_header
Create complete HTML document structure in .header.html with DOCTYPE, html, head, and body tags. Requires Apache IndexOptions +SuppressHTMLPreamble.
.SH ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
.TP
.B MARKDOWN
Alternative markdown filter command. Default: b4markdown
.TP
.B MARKDOWN_CSS
Relative path to CSS file for styling. Default: /.markdown.css
.SH FILES
.TP
.B README.md
Source markdown file
.TP
.B .header.html
Generated HTML header file
.TP
.B .readme.html
Generated full README HTML
.TP
.B .imageindex
Optional image index file (auto-generated and removed after use)
.SH DEPENDENCIES
Requires b4markdown (or alternative MARKDOWN processor) and markdown_py to be available in PATH.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Generate HTML files:
.B generate_html
.TP
Create complete HTML header:
.B generate_html \-\-create_header
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR b4markdown (1),
.BR generate_files (1),
.BR autoreadme (1)
.SH AUTHOR
AutoReadme project